WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.359 --> 00:00:04.330
AMNA NAWAZ: We return now to today's vote
in the House on a resolution denouncing bigotry

00:00:04.330 --> 00:00:05.770
in many forms.

00:00:05.770 --> 00:00:10.410
Nick Schifrin looks now at the path to this
divisive debate on Capitol Hill.

00:00:10.410 --> 00:00:16.680
NICK SCHIFRIN: For years, Minnesota Democrat
Ilhan Omar has criticized Israeli policies.

00:00:16.680 --> 00:00:21.360
As a candidate, she argued that criticism
wasn't the same as criticism of Jews.

00:00:21.360 --> 00:00:22.360
REP.

00:00:22.360 --> 00:00:26.900
ILHAN OMAR (D), Minnesota: I see there being
a difference between criticism of a country,

00:00:26.900 --> 00:00:33.550
criticism of its administration and its government,
and criticism of the people and their faith.

00:00:33.550 --> 00:00:37.250
NICK SCHIFRIN: But, in February, Republicans
targeted her Israel comments.

00:00:37.250 --> 00:00:41.440
And she said she was being attacked because
-- quote -- "It's all about the Benjamins,

00:00:41.440 --> 00:00:45.220
baby," suggesting $100 bills created support
for Israel.

00:00:45.220 --> 00:00:49.520
When asked who she thought was paying U.S.
politicians to be pro-Israel, she replied,

00:00:49.520 --> 00:00:54.470
the powerful lobbying group AIPAC, the American
Israel Public Affairs Committee.

00:00:54.470 --> 00:00:59.670
Her critics accused her of repeating anti-Semitic
tropes linking Jewish influence to money.

00:00:59.670 --> 00:01:04.180
By the next day, she deleted the tweets, but
Republican Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy

00:01:04.180 --> 00:01:05.470
has called her criticism inappropriate.

00:01:05.470 --> 00:01:06.470
REP.

00:01:06.470 --> 00:01:08.450
KEVIN MCCARTHY (R-CA), House Minority Leader:
The language they are using is wrong.

00:01:08.450 --> 00:01:11.901
And I would say their leadership is wrong
for not standing up to it.

00:01:11.901 --> 00:01:17.140
It is unacceptable in this country, especially
when you sit back and you thought about and

00:01:17.140 --> 00:01:20.659
you listened to what this country went through
in World War II.

00:01:20.659 --> 00:01:24.490
NICK SCHIFRIN: The same day, her own party
issued a statement saying her -- quote -- "use

00:01:24.490 --> 00:01:29.939
of anti-Semitic tropes and prejudicial accusations
about Israel's supporters is deeply offensive."

00:01:29.939 --> 00:01:36.150
Omar, who is Muslim and black, issued a statement
thanking her colleagues for -- quote -- "educating

00:01:36.150 --> 00:01:39.330
me on the painful history of anti-Semitic
tropes."

00:01:39.330 --> 00:01:43.729
She said, "I unequivocally apologize," but
also criticized the -- quote -- "problematic

00:01:43.729 --> 00:01:48.170
role of lobbyists in our politics."

00:01:48.170 --> 00:01:49.409
It's not the first time she's apologized.

00:01:49.409 --> 00:01:55.900
During the 2012 conflict in Gaza between Israel
and Hamas, she tweeted: "Israel has hypnotized

00:01:55.900 --> 00:01:56.900
the world.

00:01:56.900 --> 00:02:01.030
May Allah awaken the people and help them
see the evil doings of Israel."

00:02:01.030 --> 00:02:04.259
In January, she labeled that tweet unfortunate
and offensive.

00:02:04.259 --> 00:02:06.610
But President Trump said those apologies weren't
enough.

00:02:06.610 --> 00:02:11.959
DONALD TRUMP, President of the United States:
What she said is so deep-seated in her heart

00:02:11.959 --> 00:02:18.000
that her lame apology -- and that's what it
was, it was lame and she didn't mean a word

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:21.380
of it -- was just not appropriate.

00:02:21.380 --> 00:02:26.230
NICK SCHIFRIN: Nearly a month later, at an
event with Michigan Democrat Rashida Tlaib,

00:02:26.230 --> 00:02:28.640
Omar was asked about U.S. policy toward Israel.

00:02:28.640 --> 00:02:29.640
REP.

00:02:29.640 --> 00:02:36.819
ILHAN OMAR: I want to talk about the political
influence in this country that says it is

00:02:36.819 --> 00:02:38.333
OK to for people to push for allegiance to
a foreign country.

00:02:38.333 --> 00:02:49.600
I want to ask, why it is OK for me to talk
about the influence of the NRA or fossil fuel

00:02:49.600 --> 00:02:58.459
industries or big pharma, and not talk about
a powerful lobbying group that is influencing

00:02:58.459 --> 00:02:59.459
policy?

00:02:59.459 --> 00:03:03.390
NICK SCHIFRIN: Her critics called her reference
to allegiance an anti-Semitic trope, accusing

00:03:03.390 --> 00:03:07.910
Jews of having more loyalty to each other
than to their own countries.

00:03:07.910 --> 00:03:14.470
On the same day, a poster brought to a Republican
event in West Virginia linked her to 9/11.

00:03:14.470 --> 00:03:19.100
By today's vote, Democrats expanded their
resolution from anti-Semitism to condemning

00:03:19.100 --> 00:03:21.069
bigotry in many forms.

00:03:21.069 --> 00:03:22.380
Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi:

00:03:22.380 --> 00:03:23.380
REP.

00:03:23.380 --> 00:03:26.769
NANCY PELOSI (D-CA), Speaker of the House:
It is in the spirit of unity and solidarity

00:03:26.769 --> 00:03:32.909
with my colleagues, as we come together in
this chamber of our American democracy to

00:03:32.909 --> 00:03:40.550
condemn all forms of hatred, racism, prejudice,
and discrimination with a hopefully single

00:03:40.550 --> 00:03:41.650
and strong voice.

00:03:41.650 --> 00:03:46.990
NICK SCHIFRIN: And the vote specifically condemned
anti-Semitism, Islamophobia and all forms

00:03:46.990 --> 00:03:47.990
of hate.

00:03:47.990 --> 00:03:52.730
Now we get the views from leaders of two politically
active Jewish organizations in Washington.

00:03:52.730 --> 00:03:57.720
Jeremy Ben-Ami is founder and president of
J Street, which describes itself as a pro-Israel,

00:03:57.720 --> 00:04:00.280
pro-peace advocacy organization.

00:04:00.280 --> 00:04:04.409
And Josh Block, chief executive officer of
The Israel Project, which describes itself

00:04:04.409 --> 00:04:09.300
as an educational organization dedicated to
informing the media and the public about Israel

00:04:09.300 --> 00:04:10.300
and the Middle East.

00:04:10.300 --> 00:04:14.599
He worked at the American Israel Public Affairs
Committee, known as AIPAC, for nearly a decade.

00:04:14.599 --> 00:04:17.469
Thank you both for being on "NewsHour."

00:04:17.469 --> 00:04:19.139
Josh Block, let me start with you.

00:04:19.139 --> 00:04:24.240
Ilhan Omar says she's trying to criticize
Israeli policy, she's trying to criticize

00:04:24.240 --> 00:04:28.960
the role of Jewish lobby groups, specifically
AIPAC, in Washington.

00:04:28.960 --> 00:04:29.960
What is wrong with that?

00:04:29.960 --> 00:04:33.389
JOSH BLOCK, CEO, The Israel Project: There
is nothing wrong with making policy concerns

00:04:33.389 --> 00:04:37.860
about Israel known, or even suggesting you
think that the other folks in the political

00:04:37.860 --> 00:04:39.539
process are wrong.

00:04:39.539 --> 00:04:44.759
I think the trouble here is that there's been
a pattern of using specific language that

00:04:44.759 --> 00:04:49.610
seeks to marginalize and stigmatize Jewish
participation in the political process, in

00:04:49.610 --> 00:04:52.220
a way that's very dangerous for Jews.

00:04:52.220 --> 00:04:55.259
This kind of language that we have seen seep
into the political process in the United Kingdom

00:04:55.259 --> 00:04:58.340
is creating a climate that's unsafe for Jews.

00:04:58.340 --> 00:05:03.080
And I think we need to be very conscious here
of the need to stand up and make sure that

00:05:03.080 --> 00:05:08.740
the kinds of anti-Semitic language, tropes,
ideas don't cloud the conversation when it

00:05:08.740 --> 00:05:12.379
comes to the discussion of Israel, which is
a legitimate and important policy conversation

00:05:12.379 --> 00:05:13.379
to have.

00:05:13.379 --> 00:05:14.379
NICK SCHIFRIN: Jeremy Ben-Ami, is the language
dangerous?

00:05:14.379 --> 00:05:17.289
JEREMY BEN-AMI, Founder and President, J Street:
Well, I think we can all agree that there

00:05:17.289 --> 00:05:20.249
is serious anti-Semitism in this country.

00:05:20.249 --> 00:05:23.110
It's a scourge that I think we're going to
continue to fight for the rest of our lives

00:05:23.110 --> 00:05:24.360
and beyond.

00:05:24.360 --> 00:05:29.879
But I think the larger question for the society
right now is, where does this atmosphere of

00:05:29.879 --> 00:05:32.389
hate and intolerance and racism come from?

00:05:32.389 --> 00:05:36.360
There is an atmosphere that's been created
in this country, and it starts at the top

00:05:36.360 --> 00:05:38.369
with the president of the United States.

00:05:38.369 --> 00:05:40.310
And it has been created across the board.

00:05:40.310 --> 00:05:41.909
It's not simply about anti-Semitism.

00:05:41.909 --> 00:05:46.789
It's affected people of Muslim faiths, people
of color, and we have an atmosphere right

00:05:46.789 --> 00:05:52.649
now that white nationalism, white supremacy
coming from the right politically has created

00:05:52.649 --> 00:05:54.409
the atmosphere in which we're operating.

00:05:54.409 --> 00:05:55.460
That needs to be called out.

00:05:55.460 --> 00:05:59.009
NICK SCHIFRIN: Josh Block, can we get to some
of the substance of what Ilhan Omar...

00:05:59.009 --> 00:06:00.009
(CROSSTALK)

00:06:00.009 --> 00:06:01.009
JOSH BLOCK: Yes, sure.

00:06:01.009 --> 00:06:02.963
I just want to say, I think the problem with
the framing of the conversation in the way

00:06:02.963 --> 00:06:06.599
of right, left is, it really gets to the issue.

00:06:06.599 --> 00:06:12.349
The problem is anti-Semitism and the language
that seeks to ostracize, delegitimize and

00:06:12.349 --> 00:06:15.429
disenfranchise Jewish participation in the
political process.

00:06:15.429 --> 00:06:17.340
And that language is insidious.

00:06:17.340 --> 00:06:19.699
And it needs to be singled out and stopped.

00:06:19.699 --> 00:06:23.909
And so when we then suggest that critics who
have objected to Ilhan Omar's remarks in February

00:06:23.909 --> 00:06:25.289
were from the right, they weren't.

00:06:25.289 --> 00:06:29.279
The two Democratic members of Congress who
sparked the discussion were Democrats.

00:06:29.279 --> 00:06:31.650
The concerns are being voiced by Jerry Nadler.

00:06:31.650 --> 00:06:38.009
We missed in the package earlier her tweet
to a senior member, Nita Lowey, in which she

00:06:38.009 --> 00:06:40.979
accused her of being a dual loyalist.

00:06:40.979 --> 00:06:42.830
The language is -- I think Jeremy is right.

00:06:42.830 --> 00:06:45.099
There is a problem in our society.

00:06:45.099 --> 00:06:48.210
Jews are targeted six out of 10 times by religiously
motivated hate crimes.

00:06:48.210 --> 00:06:51.439
They are the number-one target of those crimes
per capita in the country.

00:06:51.439 --> 00:06:54.469
Unfortunately, that's been the case for two
decades.

00:06:54.469 --> 00:06:58.360
It's not just since the election of -- this
last presidential election.

00:06:58.360 --> 00:07:03.360
We need to be honest about the virality of
this hate and confront it on both sides.

00:07:03.360 --> 00:07:07.580
And we should be clear, all bigotry and racism
has no place in the discussion.

00:07:07.580 --> 00:07:13.589
NICK SCHIFRIN: Jeremy Ben-Ami, I want to bring
the Israeli government into this conversation.

00:07:13.589 --> 00:07:18.699
Many journalists who have lived in Jerusalem,
including me, have been accused of anti-Semitism

00:07:18.699 --> 00:07:21.629
for criticizing Israeli policies.

00:07:21.629 --> 00:07:26.469
Do you believe the Israeli government has
encouraged the idea that critics of Israel

00:07:26.469 --> 00:07:27.469
are anti-Semitic?

00:07:27.469 --> 00:07:32.880
JEREMY BEN-AMI: Well, I think there is a pattern,
and there are some in Israeli politics, I

00:07:32.880 --> 00:07:37.179
think there are some in the politics of this
country, who do try to weaponize the charge

00:07:37.179 --> 00:07:39.909
of anti-Semitism in order to shut down debate.

00:07:39.909 --> 00:07:42.729
And I think there are instances where language
goes too far.

00:07:42.729 --> 00:07:45.669
And I would agree with Josh, there are those
instances.

00:07:45.669 --> 00:07:50.330
But there are many other instances and many
more where the charge of anti-Semitism is

00:07:50.330 --> 00:07:55.240
used in order to delegitimize the critic or
the journalist or the person who is talking,

00:07:55.240 --> 00:07:56.900
and it does shut down debate.

00:07:56.900 --> 00:08:00.089
It stifles the discussion of the actual issues
that matter.

00:08:00.089 --> 00:08:02.659
How do we best end the Israeli-Palestinian
conflict?

00:08:02.659 --> 00:08:07.409
What are the actions that can be taken to
help Palestinians and Israelis find a better

00:08:07.409 --> 00:08:08.409
future?

00:08:08.409 --> 00:08:11.709
And, sometimes, we can't have that discussion
because the, first time you criticize Israel

00:08:11.709 --> 00:08:12.999
you're called an anti-Semite.

00:08:12.999 --> 00:08:15.999
NICK SCHIFRIN: Josh Block, is that debate
being scuttled by people who are using the

00:08:15.999 --> 00:08:16.999
word anti-Semite too much?

00:08:16.999 --> 00:08:20.752
JOSH BLOCK: I think it's a specious argument
to suggest that there's no criticism of Israel

00:08:20.752 --> 00:08:24.599
or that criticism of Israel is regularly stifled
by such accusations.

00:08:24.599 --> 00:08:33.129
In fact, I think what we see is, again, the
weaponization of this dialogue by folks on

00:08:33.129 --> 00:08:37.459
both the left and the right who are seeking
to advance their political gain.

00:08:37.459 --> 00:08:43.509
I think that we ought to focus on repairing
the breach and educating those about the need

00:08:43.509 --> 00:08:47.660
to engage in civil dialogue around these policy
issues.

00:08:47.660 --> 00:08:53.850
Now, again, I think it's certainly the case
that we want to see evolution in Ilhan Omar's

00:08:53.850 --> 00:08:55.440
views.

00:08:55.440 --> 00:09:00.360
But I have to say, I'm deeply alarmed by the
resistance that we all saw in the Democratic

00:09:00.360 --> 00:09:03.620
Caucus to moving forward swiftly and clearly
in a denunciation.

00:09:03.620 --> 00:09:05.660
The circus that took place is a concern.

00:09:05.660 --> 00:09:11.410
I think, for American Jews, those of us who
have believed that for, however many decades,

00:09:11.410 --> 00:09:15.040
that the elected officials United States would
act unequivocally and forcefully without delay

00:09:15.040 --> 00:09:20.430
in any way to confront these things, we should
pause for a moment and really reflect on where

00:09:20.430 --> 00:09:23.740
we are as a society and how much more we have
to do.

00:09:23.740 --> 00:09:26.509
NICK SCHIFRIN: Jeremy Ben-Ami, I want to bring
up President Trump.

00:09:26.509 --> 00:09:28.199
You mentioned him before.

00:09:28.199 --> 00:09:34.709
A couple of incidents here during the campaign,
he tweeted an ad with Hillary Clinton -- there

00:09:34.709 --> 00:09:38.360
it is -- "Most Corrupt Candidate Ever" inside
the Star of David.

00:09:38.360 --> 00:09:43.000
His closing ad during the campaign -- I think
we have got some stills of that -- he talked

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:48.589
about money and global special interests over
video of those three people, prominent Jews.

00:09:48.589 --> 00:09:54.279
More recently, in Charlottesville, when white
supremacists chanted "Death to Jews" there,

00:09:54.279 --> 00:09:58.399
the president said there were fine people
on both sides, and more recently suggested

00:09:58.399 --> 00:10:04.629
activist George Soros, who's Jewish, might
have funded the campaign -- or the caravan,

00:10:04.629 --> 00:10:06.279
rather, coming up from Mexico.

00:10:06.279 --> 00:10:07.930
Is that accelerating anti-Semitism?

00:10:07.930 --> 00:10:08.930
JEREMY BEN-AMI: Oh, absolutely.

00:10:08.930 --> 00:10:11.770
I mean, I think that the tone for the country
is set at the top.

00:10:11.770 --> 00:10:17.550
And, unfortunately, I think that this president
and some of the enablers around him -- and,

00:10:17.550 --> 00:10:21.330
in this case, unfortunately, it is within
the Republican Party, and it is on Capitol

00:10:21.330 --> 00:10:26.709
Hill and in the White House -- they are enabling
an atmosphere in which this kind of hate is

00:10:26.709 --> 00:10:27.709
festering.

00:10:27.709 --> 00:10:34.389
And the Pittsburgh shooter wasn't motivated
by tweets that were critical of Israeli policy.

00:10:34.389 --> 00:10:39.519
The Pittsburgh shooter was motivated by this
atmosphere of anti-immigrant, anti-Jewish

00:10:39.519 --> 00:10:43.139
hatred that has been fomented and made possible.

00:10:43.139 --> 00:10:49.389
And I don't see the Republican Caucus engaging
in kind of condemnation of the president that

00:10:49.389 --> 00:10:50.389
we see here.

00:10:50.389 --> 00:10:52.760
NICK SCHIFRIN: Very quickly from both of you,
are you worried that Israel is becoming a

00:10:52.760 --> 00:10:53.760
partisan issue?

00:10:53.760 --> 00:10:58.680
We have got a new generation of Democrats,
younger, more progressive, who are more interested

00:10:58.680 --> 00:10:59.680
in criticizing Israel.

00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:03.230
JOSH BLOCK: Look, I think there's a unanimous
consensus among the American public that Israel

00:11:03.230 --> 00:11:05.009
is one of our closest allies in the world.

00:11:05.009 --> 00:11:06.009
That's not changing.

00:11:06.009 --> 00:11:08.840
I think we see a strong bipartisan support
for Israel in Congress.

00:11:08.840 --> 00:11:11.259
The U.S.' relationship isn't reduced to the
Israeli-Palestinian conflict.

00:11:11.259 --> 00:11:12.269
There is much more there.

00:11:12.269 --> 00:11:14.250
And so I think we will see a robust relationship
for many years to come.

00:11:14.250 --> 00:11:15.290
NICK SCHIFRIN: Quick answer on that?

00:11:15.290 --> 00:11:18.010
JEREMY BEN-AMI: I do think that Israel is
becoming a partisan political football.

00:11:18.010 --> 00:11:22.480
And I think that folks on the right are trying
to turn it into a culture war issue, rather

00:11:22.480 --> 00:11:23.810
than a serious policy discussion.

00:11:23.810 --> 00:11:26.800
NICK SCHIFRIN: Josh Block of The Israel Project,
Jeremy Ben-Ami of J Street, thank you very

00:11:26.800 --> 00:11:27.800
much to both.

00:11:27.800 --> 00:11:27.804
JEREMY BEN-AMI: Thank you.

